---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms & Conditions - BoardTools"
  description="Terms of Service: Free local utilities provided 'as-is' under open-source MIT terms with zero warranty obligations."
>
  <section class="max-w-[800px] w-full mx-auto px-4 py-12 flex flex-col gap-8 animate-fade-in-up">
    <!-- Breadcrumb & Header -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold text-slate uppercase">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-brand-blue">Terms & Conditions</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-display font-medium text-4xl tracking-tight text-primary mt-1">
        Terms & Conditions
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-slate">Last updated: June 25, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Legal disclaimer banner -->
    <div class="p-6 bg-surface border border-hairline-strong rounded-2xl flex flex-col gap-2">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-sm text-primary uppercase tracking-wider">Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-slate leading-relaxed font-semibold">
        BoardTools provides static code converters, checkers, and design workspaces "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" without any warranties of any kind. 
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Content Columns -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-sm text-slate leading-relaxed font-sans">
      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-4">1. Agreement to Terms</h3>
      <p>
        By accessing this website, you agree to comply with and be bound by these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree with any of these terms, you are prohibited from using or accessing this site. All components, layouts, and tools are provided for educational and utility purposes only.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-4">2. Open Source & License</h3>
      <p>
        BoardTools is inspired by Miro's workspace layouts, but is an independent utility website. Unless explicitly stated otherwise:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <li>The client-side javascript algorithms are licensed under standard open-source parameters (MIT License).</li>
        <li>You are welcome to clone, copy, run, or distribute the source code locally on your own environment.</li>
        <li>All designs, styles, logo badges, and headers remain the copyright of BoardTools.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-4">3. Limitation of Liability</h3>
      <p>
        Under no circumstances shall BoardTools or its contributors be held liable for any damages, errors, data leaks (caused by your own copy-pasting outside BoardTools), browser tab crashes, or data loss arising out of the use or inability to use the local utilities.
      </p>
      <p>
        Because our tools run entirely client-side, we have no control over:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <li>Browser extensions that may inspect your pasted text variables.</li>
        <li>Malicious keyloggers running on your operating system.</li>
        <li>Your local browser storage availability and persistence.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-4">4. Accuracy of Tools</h3>
      <p>
        While we strive to implement robust converters, JSON parsers, contrast ratio algorithms, and UUID standards:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <li>We do not guarantee that the outputs (e.g. accessibility checks, optimized SVG nodes) are 100% accurate, error-free, or legally compliant with WCAG standards.</li>
        <li>Users are solely responsible for verifying tool outcomes before deploying them to production systems.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-4">5. Revisions and Modifications</h3>
      <p>
        We may update these terms or add/remove client-side tools at any time without prior notice. By continuing to use the website, you agree to be bound by the current version of these Terms & Conditions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
